==> Restore complete. The saber should ignite on the next power-on.

    If it does not boot:
    1. Re-enter DFU (hardware BOOT+RESET always works).
    2. Verify with: dfu-util -l   (expect 0483:df11)
    3. Re-run this script.

    If it still does not boot after that — file an issue. The
    fingerprint check above is the strongest evidence we have that
    the bits are right; if those bits don't boot, the chip itself
    has a problem and ST-Link / SWD is the next step.
